    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>pizza base mix</strong> to a large bowl</p><p>Gradually add up to 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[225ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>warm water</strong> (you may not need all of it), a little at a time, and gently mix with a plastic spatula until a sticky dough ball has formed</p><p>Tip the dough ball out onto a <strong>lightly floured </strong>work surface and knead it for 5 min or until a smooth dough forms, then cover the dough all over with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and cover with <strong>cling film</strong> and set aside for 5 min to rest</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-meat-free-chick-n-and-gochujang-scissor-cut-noodles/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Wash then cut your <strong>pak</strong> <strong>choi</strong> in half, separating the <strong>white</strong> <strong>base[s]</strong> and <strong>green</strong> <strong>tops</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Cut the <strong>white</strong> <strong>base[s]</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Shred the <strong>green</strong> <strong>tops</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-meat-free-chick-n-and-gochujang-scissor-cut-noodles/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>meat-free chick'n</strong> and cook for 5 min or until warmed through and starting to brown</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-meat-free-chick-n-and-gochujang-scissor-cut-noodles/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Fill a large pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Hold the <strong>dough </strong>with one hand and a pair of scissors with the other, cut small strips of noodles off the <strong>dough</strong> and allow them to fall into the water (be careful not to splash!), once done cutting the noodles, put the pot over a high heat and cook for 4 min or until cooked with a slight bite - these are your <strong>scissor cut noodles</strong></p><p>Once cooked, drain the noodles, reserving a cup of <strong>starchy noodle water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-meat-free-chick-n-and-gochujang-scissor-cut-noodles/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the meat-free chick'n has started to brown, add the <strong>pak</strong> <strong>choi</strong> <strong>white</strong> <strong>bases </strong>to the pan and cook for 2-3 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>pak</strong> <strong>choi</strong> <strong>green</strong> <strong>tops</strong> and give everything a good mix up until they're wilted</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-meat-free-chick-n-and-gochujang-scissor-cut-noodles/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>maple syrup</strong>, <strong>gochujang paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, <strong>soy sauce </strong>and <strong>toasted sesame oil </strong>to the pan with the meat-free chick'n</p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-meat-free-chick-n-and-gochujang-scissor-cut-noodles/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>cooked scissor cut noodles </strong>to the pan with a splash of <strong>reserved starchy noodle water</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up until fully coated \u2013 this is your <strong>spicy meat-free chick'n & gochujang scissor cut noodles</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-meat-free-chick-n-and-gochujang-scissor-cut-noodles/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>spicy meat-free chick'n & gochujang scissor cut noodles</strong></p><p>Garnish with your <strong>toasted sesame seeds</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
